feather /ˈfɛðə/

(feathers) 

1. N-COUNT A bird's feathers are the soft covering on its body. Each feather consists of a lot of smooth hairs on each side of a thin stiff centre. 羽毛 

例： ...a hat that she had made herself from black ostrich feathers. …她用黑色鸵鸟羽毛为自己做的一顶帽子。 

2.  →  see also feathered 

3. to ruffle someone's feathers→see ruffle

